    <section id="id4630375">
      <title>REINFORCING STRUCTURES</title>
      <para id="id8323853">Activity 1</para>
      <para id="id15022977">How do we reinforce structures?</para>
      <list id="id14229779" list-type="bulleted">
        <item>Rectangular objects are not necessarily sturdy. A rectangle can convert to a rhombus quite easily when force is exerted on it. The triangle is the figure that provides the greatest degree of stability. Consider the framework of a bicycle. Are there any triangles?</item>
      </list>
      <para id="id5821034">
        <figure id="id15152063">
          <media id="id15152063_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Picture 1-3ea8.png" id="id15152063__onlineimage" height="302" width="460"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
      </para>
      <figure id="id11779431">
        <media id="id11779431_media" alt="">
          <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/Picture 2-d039.png" id="id11779431__onlineimage" height="211" width="514"/>
